Return the row and column indices of the cell that overlaps the pixel at the specified grid coordinate. If no such cell exists, null is returned.  <p>The example function below uses this method to compute the value of the <code>dataField</code> for a grid cell.</p> <pre>
 function getCellData(x:Number, y:Number):Object
 {
 var cell:CellPosition = getCellAt(x, y);
 if (!cell)
 return null;
 var GridColumn:column = grid.columns.getItemAt(cell.columnIndex);
 return grid.dataProvider.getItemAt(cell.rowIndex)[column.dataField];
 }
 </pre>
